news.title: NCLT admits insolvency proceedings against AVIOM India Housing Finance
news.para: Upon admission of the petition for CIRP against AVIOM (order dated February 20, 2025), the RBI on Friday said it has decided that the three-member committee shall continue as the advisory committee.

news.title: CapitaLand India Trust to invest Rs 1,000 crore in MAIA Estates' project in Bengaluru
news.para: Upon completion of the development and stabilisation, CapitaLand India Trust is expected to acquire the office space in H1 2030, while Maia Group will retain the retail portion. The purchase price of the office space is estimated to be Rs 14,717 million.

news.title: Builders FirstSource reports net sales of $3.82 billion in Q4 2024
news.para: Many potential homebuyers remain reluctant to buy due to still-high mortgage rates, with the benchmark 30-year fixed-rate mortgage hovering around 6.9% as of December-end.

news.title: Lower prices attract real estate investors to Rome
news.para: Pezzano's property hunt highlights a wider shift that has put Rome in the sights of professional real estate investors, after the Milan area took more than half of their investments in Italy in the past five years, based on data by Scenari Immobiliari think-tank.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body forms new waste management rules for large residential colonies
news.para: The rules promote decentralised waste processing methods like composting, vermicomposting and bio-methanation, aiming to reduce the burden on centralised facilities and landfills. Currently, large townships, hotels, and clubs are required to manage their waste.

news.title: Casagrand Millenia acquires 1.18 hectare land in Pune for Rs 126 crore
news.para: The transaction incurred a stamp duty of Rs 8.82 crore and a registration fee of Rs 30,000, according to the Inspector General of Registration (IGR) documents reviewed by Square Yards. The transaction was registered in January 2025.

news.title: Mohali villagers threaten protest if building bylaws notices not revoked
news.para: The Mohali municipal corporation had issued notices regarding building regulations to residents of several villages, including Mohali, Sohana, Kumbra, Mator, Shahi Majra and Madanpur, under the newly implemented building bylaws.

news.title: Telangana HC raps Hydraa’s ‘unilateral’ demolitions
news.para: The court was hearing a petition filed by Alagiri Praveen of Muthangi village in the Patancheru area, which falls under Tellapur municipality.

news.title: Mumbai: SGNP authorities hold hearing to check eligibility of 7,000 slum dwellers for free housing
news.para: Notices for the hearing and to submit documents were issued after the Jan 15 order of Bombay high court, ordering the state to find alternative land for rehabilitation of encroachers.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body launch e-khata drive for unauthorised properties
news.para: Within MCC limits, the facility to issue e-khata using e-property software was implemented in 2022. As many as 39,000 e-khatas were already created and distributed to property owners.

news.title: Maharashtra CM orders investigation into a housing project in Jalna
news.para: The Maharashtra Chief Minister Office has asked CIDCO to start a probe into allegations that a housing project worth ₹900 crore, that was scrapped in 2000 for being unviable.

news.title: Soon, online registrations of mortgage, lease deeds in Gujarat
news.para: ​Dipak Patel, president, Credai-Gujarat, said, "Home loan takers need to register mortgage deeds with banks, and so do people taking mortgage loans."

news.title: Maharashtra minister urges Mhada to accelerate affordable housing initiatives
news.para: Minister of state for housing Pankaj Bhoyar proposed that these houses be allocated to the police department, instructing officials to coordinate in this regard and submit a formal proposal.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government doubles PMAY-Rural allocation to Rs 4,882 crore
news.para: The state govt earmarked Rs 4,882 crore for the scheme in 2025-26 fiscal. This was just double of Rs 2,441 crore allocated in 2024-25.

news.title: Speculators out, end-users back to stabilise home prices in Hyderabad
news.para: A stable rate card for apartments, especially those set to be completed in the next 6 to 12 months, with average prices hovering in the Rs 8,000 to Rs 10,000 (semi-luxury segment) per square feet (sft) range.

news.title: Odisha government accelerates urban development initiatives to achieve 2036 vision
news.para: A high-level meeting chaired by housing and urban development minister Krushna Chandra Mahapatra was held on Thursday at Kharavela Bhavan to discuss various urban development initiatives.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body launches amnesty scheme for property tax defaulters
news.para: The scheme was implemented on 24th February and will continue until 18th March. This initiative will help the civic body effectively recover arrears of property tax within the UMC jurisdiction, said a UMC official.

news.title: US-based CoStar prepares $1.7 billion bid for Australia's Domain: Source
news.para: CoStar declined to comment. Domain, which is about 60% owned by Australian media group Nine Entertainment, did not immediately respond to a request for comment from Reuters.

news.title: Sebi proposes framework for fast track follow-on offer by REITs, InvITs
news.para: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) has sought public comments by March 13 on the proposals.
